05/04/2006
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- Greek Foreign Minister Dora Bakoyannis kicked off a three-day visit to Nicosia on Tuesday (4 April) saying resolution of the Cyprus issue is a top foreign policy priority. She also said a new effort has been launched to reunify the ethnically divided island since the February meeting between Cypriot President Tassos Papadopoulos and UN Secretary General Kofi Annan in Paris. This is her first visit to Cyprus since being appointed foreign minister in February. (Kathimerini - 05/04/06; ANA, MPA - 04/04/06) 
